" <i>Glory, glory,
hallelujah!</i> "

272
00:26:44,710 --> 00:26:48,810
" <i>Glory, glory,
hallelujah!</i> "

273
00:26:49,210 --> 00:26:52,810
" <i>Glory, glory,
hallelujah!</i> "

274
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:57,000
" <i>His truth is
marching ooon</i> "

275
00:26:57,210 --> 00:27:01,010
" <i>He has sounded forth the trumpet
that shall never call retreat;</i> "

276
00:27:01,210 --> 00:27:05,210
" <i>he is sifting out the hearts of men
before his judgment seat; </i>"

277
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,800
- Will, I just heard...
- Hello Herb.

278
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:21,670
You can count on me,
you know that, don't you?

279
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:24,640
- I was figuring I might.
- You cleaned this town up.

280
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,850
You made it fit
for women and kids to live in.

281
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:29,220
Miller or nobody else'll never
drag it down again.

282
00:27:29,470 --> 00:27:33,100
- I hoping people'd feel that way.
- What other way is there?

283
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:37,650
- How many men you got lined up?
- None yet.

284
00:27:40,070 --> 00:27:45,450
Well, you better get going, man. I'll be back
in 10 minutes. Loaded for bear.

285
00:27:56,450 --> 00:28:01,450
[Snoring]

286
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,160
[Knock on door]

287
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:17,850
Where is he?

288
00:28:18,350 --> 00:28:22,650
He's coming up the back way.
There's careful man.

289
00:28:22,950 --> 00:28:24,550
[Knock on door]

290
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:29,780
- Come in, Mr Weaver.
- Hello Mrs. Ramirez.

291
00:28:29,990 --> 00:28:31,580
- Hello. Sit down, please.
- Thanks

292
00:28:34,460 --> 00:28:36,710
- Is there anything wrong, Mrs Ramirez?
- No.

293
00:28:36,810 --> 00:28:38,710
Then,
why did you send for me?

294
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,300
I'm leaving town.
I want to sell the store.

295
00:28:41,550 --> 00:28:44,930
- You want to buy me out?
- Well, how much did you want?

296
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:47,850
Two thousand.
I think that's fair.

297
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:51,480
It's fair alright, 
but I couldn't raise that much right now.

298
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:55,520
- How much can you raise?
- Oh... 1000 dollars.

299
00:28:57,480 --> 00:29:01,150
All right you can pay Sam the rest
in six months.

300
00:29:01,450 --> 00:29:05,370
- He'll get it to me. A deal?
- Yes, ma'am.

301
00:29:05,570 --> 00:29:08,750
All right, Mr Weaver.
Thank you.

302
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:15,250
Mrs Ramirez, I want to
thank you for everything, I mean...

303
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:19,670
When you first put the deal to me
about staking me in the store,

304
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:23,640
and being a silent partner,
you know, my wife thought...

305
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:31,520
Err... What I really mean to say is that
you've been real decent to me right along,

306
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:33,690
and I want you to know
that I've been honest with you.

307
00:29:33,850 --> 00:29:36,520
I know you have, Mr Weaver.
Goodbye.

308
00:29:36,730 --> 00:29:39,900
Goodbye, Mrs Ramirez.
And good luck to you.

309
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:40,900
Thank you.

310
00:29:55,330 --> 00:29:58,510
- Will..
- Amy. You've changed your mind.

311
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:04,140
I thought you'd
changed yours.

312
00:30:06,300 --> 00:30:08,560
No, Will,
I have my ticket.

313
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:14,020
I see.

314
00:30:14,860 --> 00:30:18,570
Clean number 19.
Mrs Miller is very particular.

315
00:30:18,820 --> 00:30:22,410
- Is Helen Ramirez in?
- I guess so.

316
00:30:23,150 --> 00:30:26,240
Think you can find it
alright?

317
00:30:33,420 --> 00:30:34,820
[Knock on door]

318
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,210
Come in.

319
00:30:48,310 --> 00:30:51,690
What are you looking at?
You think I have changed?

320
00:30:55,810 --> 00:30:59,190
Well, what do you want?
You want me to help you?

321
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:02,610
You want me to ask Frank to let you go?
You want me to beg for you?

322
00:31:02,860 --> 00:31:06,120
I would not do it.
I would not lift a finger for you.

323
00:31:07,580 --> 00:31:11,210
I came to tell you he was coming.
I should've figured you know about it.

324
00:31:11,460 --> 00:31:12,960
I know about it.

325
00:31:13,120 --> 00:31:17,710
You ought to get out of town
or I might not be able to...well..

326
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:20,880
- Anything can happen.
- I'm not afraid of him.

327
00:31:21,130 --> 00:31:25,890
I know you're not but you...
you know how he is.

328
00:31:27,050 --> 00:31:29,220
I know
how he is.

329
00:31:31,060 --> 00:31:33,980
Maybe he doesn't know.

330
00:31:34,190 --> 00:31:38,030
- He's probably got letters.
- What about it?

331
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:45,660
Nothing in life is free.
I'm getting out. I'm packing.

332
00:31:45,870 --> 00:31:47,500
That's good.

333
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:54,500
[In Spanish]
One day, mister.

334
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:57,500
Sí, Rosa.

335
00:32:03,260 --> 00:32:05,890
- Goodbye, Helen.
- Kane...

336
00:32:06,930 --> 00:32:10,180
If you're smart,
you will get out, too.

337
00:32:11,810 --> 00:32:14,190
- I can't.
- I know.

338
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:48,470
- May I ask you something?
- Sure.

339
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:51,940
- Who is Miss Ramirez?
- Mrs Ramirez?

340
00:32:53,100 --> 00:32:56,020
She used to be a friend of your husband's
a while back.

341
00:32:56,230 --> 00:32:59,610
Before that
she was a friend of Frank Miller's.

342
00:32:59,820 --> 00:33:02,990
I see.
Thank you.

343
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:08,160
- You don't like my husband, do you?
- No.

344
00:33:08,330 --> 00:33:11,000
- Why?
- Lots of reasons.

345
00:33:11,210 --> 00:33:14,790
One thing, this place was always busy
when Frank Miller was around.

346
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,380
I'm not the only one.

347
00:33:16,630 --> 00:33:20,170
There's plenty of people think
he's got a comeuppance coming.

348
00:33:20,340 --> 00:33:23,590
You asked me, ma'am,
so I'm telling you.

349
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:49,040
- I'll go and get some liquor.
- You have to have it?

350
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:51,250
- Yeah.
- If you're going after that...

351
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:55,250
- I said I was going for liquor.
- Keep away from Kane.

352
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:57,170
Sure,
I can wait.

353
00:34:11,670 --> 00:34:13,170
Cowboy:
Hiya, Harvey.

354
00:34:25,620 --> 00:34:29,080
Hello, Harv.
Where's the tin star?

355
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:33,670
- I turned it in and quit.
- Smart move.

356
00:34:34,920 --> 00:34:37,340
I didn't ask you
for your opinion.

357
00:35:04,530 --> 00:35:07,160
Hey, Ben!
How are you?

358
00:35:08,450 --> 00:35:11,330
Hey,
look who's here!

359
00:35:12,290 --> 00:35:14,830
- How are you, Ben?
- Give me a bottle.

360
00:35:19,260 --> 00:35:22,800
- It's been a long time, Ben.
- Yeah.

361
00:35:23,010 --> 00:35:24,890
- Yes, sir.
- How's Frank?

362
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:31,640
- He's not complaining.
- It'll be a hot time in the old town tonight, eh?

363
00:35:34,560 --> 00:35:36,070
I wouldn't be surprised.

364
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:33,000
I'll give you odds Kane's dead five minutes
after Frank gets off the train.

365
00:36:33,210 --> 00:36:36,750
- It's not much time.
- That's all Frank'll need, because I...

366
00:36:51,020 --> 00:36:55,730
You carry a badge and a gun, Marshal.
You ain't got no call to do that.

367
00:36:58,150 --> 00:37:00,320
You're right.

368
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:04,320
No.

369
00:37:13,670 --> 00:37:15,630
I guess you all know
why I am here.

370
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:18,470
I need deputies.
I'll take all I can get.

371
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:26,220
You must be crazy comin' in here
to raise a posse.

372
00:37:26,390 --> 00:37:29,730
Frank's got friends in this room.
You ought to know that.

373
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:36,770
Some of you were special deputies when we
broke this bunch. I need you again...now.

374
00:37:38,900 --> 00:37:40,900
Things were different then, Kane.

375
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,490
You had six steady deputies 
to start off with.

376
00:37:43,660 --> 00:37:47,660
Every one a top gun.
You ain't got but two now.

377
00:37:47,830 --> 00:37:51,790
You ain't got two.
Harv Pell says he just quit. Why?

378
00:37:55,250 --> 00:37:56,880
That's between the two of us.

379
00:37:57,090 --> 00:38:00,760
You're asking an awful lot Kane,
considering the kind of man Frank Miller is.

380
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:04,510
All right
We all know what Miller's like.

381
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:07,310
That's why I'm here.
How about it?

382
00:38:31,310 --> 00:38:35,310
[Crowd begins laughing]

383
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:57,310
" <i>He made a vow
while in state prison</i> "

384
00:38:57,750 --> 00:39:00,310
" <i>Vowed it would be my life
or his'n</i>  "

385
00:39:00,810 --> 00:39:03,310
" <i>I'm not afraid of death
but oh</i> "

386
00:39:03,810 --> 00:39:10,310
" <i>What will I do
if you leeeave me?</i> "

